Fulda, Germany - A homeowner in the German state of Hesse woke up to find his front entrance bricked up, according to a police report from Tuesday.As the man opened his front door in the village of Mainhausen in order to leave the house on Monday morning, he was confronted with a brick wall.In order to leave the house, he had to tear the wall down, police said.&quot;We don't know if it was a prank. It could also be revenge or a dare,&quot; police spokesman Ingbert Zacharias said.Police officers are working on the assumption that there are several perpetrators.ANA-dpa